{
  "stem": "2833.3",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then we had to also stand every day outside, and it was still cold, for counting.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in the meantime, they-- we had sort of an old broom.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We were supposed to sweep a little bit between the rows of the-- where we were lying.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So she said, OK, from now on, you don't go outside in the morning, you sweep.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because it was much easier for me to do that than to stand in the cold for two or three hours.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So she really saved my life in a way, because I was at the end of my strength.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the potato peels and the sweeping of the barrack instead of standing outside was another guardian angel.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And that's how I made it through till we heard the Americans are coming.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the SS ran away and we were guarded by old men.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was a-- I don't know what they called the group, but they were all, you know, older men in their 50s who didn't even know what they were doing with us.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They were scared of us, because they were outnumbered and they figured those women could do something.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Which we didn't, couldn't have the strength.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But they were scared of us, and the SS had run away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And our barracks were surrounded-- I was in the lower one-- by woods.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And they were hiding in the woods there because they didn't want to be found by the Americans when they come, which they eventually did.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And I had a very lovely experience, because there was all of a sudden a GI standing at the gate instead of a German.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And I wanted to walk out to see how, you know, that is.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And he said, no, you can't.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "We are here to guard you.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
